

 DevOps Engineer – Roles & Responsibilities

 1. CI/CD Pipeline Engineering

 Design, build, and maintain CI/CD pipelines using Harness, GitHub
 Automate build, test, scan, and deployment workflows
 Implement pipeline-as-code and reusable templates
 Enable fast, reliable, and repeatable deployments



 2. Infrastructure as Code & Automation

 Develop and maintain infrastructure automation using:

   Terraform
   Ansible
 Integrate IaC into CI/CD pipelines
 Enforce consistency across environments (dev, test, prod)



 3. Cloud & Platform Enablement

 Enable application teams to deploy workloads on AWS, Azure, and GCP
 Provide standardized deployment patterns
 Manage environment configurations and secrets
 Support container and VM-based workloads



 4. Configuration & Release Management

 Manage application configuration across environments
 Implement versioning and rollback strategies
 Support blue-green, canary, and rolling deployments
 Coordinate releases with multiple teams



 5. Observability & Operational Support

 Integrate monitoring, logging, and alerting into pipelines
 Ensure deployments are observable and debuggable
 Support production issues related to deployments and automation
 Improve reliability of delivery pipelines



 6. Security & Compliance in the Pipeline

 Embed security into CI/CD (DevSecOps):

   Image scanning
   Dependency scanning
   Secrets detection
 Enforce compliance checks and approvals
 Automate security controls in pipelines



 7. Container & Artifact Management

 Build, version, and publish application artifacts
 Manage container images and registries
 Maintain artifact repositories and promotion workflows
 Support multi-architecture and multi-environment deployments



 8. Developer Experience & Enablement

 Improve developer productivity through automation
 Create self-service pipelines and templates
 Maintain documentation and best practices
 Act as a bridge between development and operations teams



 9. Platform Reliability & Optimization

 Ensure CI/CD platform availability and performance
 Optimize pipeline execution time and resource usage
 Reduce deployment failures and manual interventions
 Continuously improve tooling and workflows



 10. Collaboration & Continuous Improvement

 Work closely with:

   Developers
   SRE
   Infrastructure and Platform teams
 Evaluate and adopt new DevOps tools and practices
 Drive continuous improvement in delivery processes




| Aspect           | Infrastructure Engineer   | Linux Admin / Platform | DevOps Engineer     | SRE                 |
| ---------------- | ------------------------- | ---------------------- | ------------------- | ------------------- |
| Main Question    | Is infra built correctly? | Is OS healthy?         | Can we deploy fast? | Is system reliable? |
| Works On         | Cloud infra               | Linux OS               | CI/CD & pipelines   | Prod reliability    |
| Creates VMs      | ✅ Yes                    | ❌ No                 | ❌ No              | ❌ No               |
| Configures OS    | ❌ No                     | ✅ Yes                | ❌ No              | Sometimes           |
| App Deployment   | ❌ No                     | ❌ No                 | ✅ Yes             | Reviews safety      |
| Automation Goal  | Standard infra            | Consistent OS          | Fast delivery       | Less incidents      |
| Terraform        | **Owns**                  | Reviews                | Uses                | Reviews             |
| Ansible          | Minimal                   | **Heavy**              | Moderate            | For toil            |
| Harness          | Infra pipelines           | OS pipelines           | **App pipelines**   | Release control     |
| GitHub           | Terraform code            | Ansible code           | Pipeline code       | Reliability tools   |
| Monitoring Focus | Infra health              | Host health            | Pipeline health     | **SLI/SLOs**        |
| On-call For      | Infra outages             | OS issues              | Deploy failures     | **Major incidents** |
| Success Metric   | Stable infra              | Secure OS              | Deployment speed    | Uptime & SLOs       |
